Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.81,0:00:05.90,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is a science where one understands the structure of matter, breaks it down, then rebuilds it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.90,0:00:11.53,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is not an all-powerful technique,\Nas one cannot create something out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.32,0:00:17.66,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.66,0:00:22.08,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,This is the concept of equivalent exchange, the fundamental basis of alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:26.75,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a taboo in alchemy. Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.75,0:00:29.59,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,One must not commit this act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:05.56,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Scar, a man who only targets State Alchemists,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.56,0:02:07.81,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,attacked Edward Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:12.61,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Although Ed accepted death at Scar's hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:16.82,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,his life was saved thanks to interference by Colonel Mustang and his men.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.74,0:02:21.95,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al, who discovered the joy of being alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:28.66,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,decided to return to their birthplace, Resembool, to restore their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.97,0:02:38.76,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.18,0:02:41.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.01,0:02:45.51,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The guys at Eastern Headquarters said that they were too busy to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.51,0:02:47.18,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm here to see you off instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.18,0:02:49.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine with me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.39,0:02:51.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...why is the Major...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:52.65,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural you'd get an escort.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:56.65,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Getting attacked by Scar in your state wouldn't be too pretty, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:01.32,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Just accept the Major's kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.86,0:03:03.78,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Children don't need to be reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:05.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't treat me like a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.99,0:03:08.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And Al is going to be on this ride, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:09.71,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.67,0:03:17.46,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he'd be lonely riding alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.46,0:03:18.67,Default-alt,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you take my brother for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:21.51,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.55,0:03:26.72,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Well guys, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:29.43,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever happen to stop by Central again, come say hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.72,0:04:06.47,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:08.97,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,You're Dr. Marcoh, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:12.94,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Alex Louis Armstrong from Central!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:16.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Someone you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:19.90,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,He's a talented alchemist who used to reside in Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.82,0:04:24.45,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,He was studying how to apply alchemy to medical treatment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:28.08,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,but he had been reported missing after the civil war in Ishbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.53,0:04:30.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get off here, Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:35.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling he'd know something about the transmutation of living organisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:43.55,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know someone who looks like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:45.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you're good at drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:49.93,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Drawing portraits is a skill that has been passed down in the Armstrong household for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:52.35,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dr. Mauro, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:52.93,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,"Mauro"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.27,0:04:57.35,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,We were in a tight spot because our doctors were drafted for the civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.73,0:05:00.69,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what would have happened if Dr. Mauro hadn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.15,0:05:05.20,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't abandon a single patient\Nno matter who it is. We owe him so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:08.70,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's like something flashes before your eyes,\Nand suddenly, your wounds are already healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.83,0:05:12.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This must be the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.46,0:05:17.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:18.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.00,0:05:20.38,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:22.30,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here to take me back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:24.63,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.63,0:05:26.84,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go back there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.84,0:05:27.88,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.88,0:05:29.26,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No, you've got it all wrong! We just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:31.35,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Then did you come here to seal my mouth?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:32.68,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No, we...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:34.35,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You can't trick me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:39.69,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you to please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:40.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.61,0:05:48.86,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea you were hiding out in the countryside under an assumed name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.57,0:05:54.49,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I heard a rumor you took some classified documents with you when you disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:57.12,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stand it any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:05:59.79,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it was an order from the superiors...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.13,0:06:03.00,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,...but because of it, I had to stain my hands by conducting research on such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:04.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Such a thing"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:11.26,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,So many innocent people died because of it in the civil war in Ishbal...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:17.77,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I can't atone for what I've done, even with my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.35,0:06:23.40,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided to become a doctor for this town because I wanted to do all I could to pay for my sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:30.16,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, what exactly were you ordered to research?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.66,0:06:32.91,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,The Philosopher's Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:41.33,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,The things I took with me are\Nthe research data and the stone itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:43.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You have the stone?! Here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.34,0:06:55.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a liquid, not a stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.23,0:07:02.81,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Philosopher's Stone"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.81,0:07:04.31,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Heavenly Stone"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.90,0:07:08.15,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Great Elixir"... "The Red Tincture"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:09.61,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,"The Fifth Element".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:17.37,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,They aren't necessarily in the shape of a stone,\Njust as how the stone itself has many different names.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.16,0:07:20.29,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,But this is incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:24.21,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know when it'll reach its limit and become unusable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:29.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But it definitely displayed its power during the Ishbalan war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.34,0:07:32.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Same with the bogus High Priest of Lior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:37.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,His abilities were improved,\Neven though the stone was incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:44.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If something like that can be made,\Nit's possible to perfect it if we give it more research!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.19,0:07:49.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh, please show me the research data!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:53.16,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Major... who is this boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:56.07,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,He's a State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:07:59.95,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,A boy like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:06.42,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,There were so many alchemists who gave up their state qualifications after the civil war...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:10.26,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,...because they couldn't stand being human weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:12.09,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:14.55,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:21.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm willing to go through hell until I achieve my goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:31.07,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I see... so you broke the taboo...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:34.65,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.65,0:08:38.49,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You were able to affix the soul of a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:43.66,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You just might be able to create a perfect Philosopher's Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.66,0:08:44.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:46.58,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I can't show you the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:47.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:50.09,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't desire such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:52.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's to get our bodies back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.55,0:08:53.09,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:55.51,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,That is the Devil's research.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.51,0:08:57.64,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You'll see Hell if you study it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.55,0:09:00.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen Hell already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.85,0:09:05.35,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Please, leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:21.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen Hell already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.96,0:09:28.58,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:35.26,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It's incomplete, but we could have taken at least the stone by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:40.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I wanted it. I wanted it so badly, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.39,0:09:46.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want to steal the only support the people in this town have in order to get our bodies back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.48,0:09:51.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's good enough that we found out\Na Philosopher's Stone can be created.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.69,0:09:53.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We'll look for another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:58.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But what about you, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:10:01.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have to report Dr. Marcoh to Central?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:07.12,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,The person I met today is\Na town doctor by the name of Mauro.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:10.04,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:16.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Marcoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.63,0:10:19.88,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the data is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:24.64,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,If you still feel you won't regret\Ndiscovering the truth, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:29.89,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,You may be able to reach\Nthe real truth that is beyond truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.60,0:10:33.19,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,No... this is unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.65,0:10:39.07,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I pray you boys will be able to get your bodies back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:47.58,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What does it say, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.75,0:10:51.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,National Central Library, 1st Branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.21,0:10:55.46,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Makes sense. A forest would be\Nan ideal place to hide a tree, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:59.09,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,There are enough books in there to last several lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.13,0:11:03.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can find a clue to getting the stone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:12.98,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,There you are, Marcoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:30.33,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Winry! Winry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:32.83,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You've got an old customer at the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.83,0:11:36.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:37.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.50,0:11:39.51,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,God, what happened to you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.51,0:11:42.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A lot. We're going to need your help again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.55,0:11:46.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is Major Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:48.64,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure to meet you, I'm Pinako Rockbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:54.52,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,But gosh darn, looks like Ed got shorter after not seeing him for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:12:00.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm pretty sure you're supposed to say "got taller" at times like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.86,0:12:03.15,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,If you really did, then I'd say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.15,0:12:05.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say, you minimum hag?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.08,0:12:12.04,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I tell you to give me a call\Nbefore stopping by for maintenance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:14.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You trying to kill me, Winry?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.50,0:12:18.80,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:19.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:25.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,My bad, my bad. It broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.93,0:12:27.60,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,"Broke"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:31.56,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,An automail of the highest quality... That I worked so hard on...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.56,0:12:34.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, to smithereens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.77,0:12:38.52,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And Al is broken, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.07,0:12:41.69,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck have you guys been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:47.28,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,All you ever do is worry me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.87,0:12:49.95,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.87,0:12:56.75,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,So you want to return to Central as soon as possible to get that data, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.75,0:12:59.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. So I want you to fix me up as quick as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:04.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'll need to adjust your leg,\Ntoo, and not just your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:07.01,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, seems like you've at least grown a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.01,0:13:07.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.43,0:13:12.14,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike your leg though, I'm going to have to remake your arm from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.68,0:13:14.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Will it take a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.73,0:13:16.39,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.77,0:13:19.65,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:23.82,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to bear with a spare for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:24.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.15,0:13:29.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's tough to walk when you're not used to the leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.16,0:13:31.28,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fix it up before you get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:32.74,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.74,0:13:35.79,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Materials... Assembly... Connection... Calibration...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:37.96,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be all-nighters, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.96,0:13:39.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for being so unreasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.79,0:13:43.00,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,But you want to go back to Central as soon as possible, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:45.26,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Then we'll work to make that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.26,0:13:49.01,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll charge extra for the express fee!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:00.77,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It's finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.77,0:14:02.48,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.23,0:14:06.57,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see Edward Elric around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.57,0:14:10.32,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he said that he was visiting his mother's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.46,0:14:19.33,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:23.59,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of lives have those boys been living?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.46,0:14:27.84,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even send us a single letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:33.26,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,They are famous alchemists, even in Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:37.06,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,That drags them into trouble, as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:41.31,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry. Those boys are strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:43.44,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.40,0:14:46.07,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,That makes me feel better, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.57,0:14:52.87,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Are those two like grandchildren to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.32,0:14:56.33,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I've been watching over them ever since they were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.29,0:15:01.71,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Their father was an old drinking buddy of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:06.13,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,but he left the village, leaving his wife and children behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:09.38,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if he's still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:22.19,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it, where are Miss Winry's parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:23.77,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.77,0:15:25.69,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,During the Ishbalan war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.78,0:15:31.99,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,My son... her parents... were surgeons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:36.20,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They left for the battlefield because there was a shortage of doctors, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.66,0:15:39.20,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,It was a horrible war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:41.50,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It sure was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:47.00,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:49.51,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time to start preparing supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:52.93,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you'd eat a lot,\Nso you can expect a big dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:56.22,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, I can't trouble you any further...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:15:59.43,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,A meal tastes better with more people at the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.43,0:16:02.64,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,There's an extra bed open for patients, so you can sleep there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.60,0:16:07.02,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only place those brothers can stay, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.40,0:16:09.65,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Adding an extra guest won't make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:12.03,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What about their home?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.66,0:16:16.66,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:19.33,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have a home to return to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.58,0:16:26.50,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They burnt their house down the day Ed decided to leave this village after getting his state qualification.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.63,0:16:33.30,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,They probably did it to make sure there would be no going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.72,0:16:40.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.27,0:16:43.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,They're all waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.98,0:16:48.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're ba-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.77,0:16:50.27,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.65,0:16:56.28,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Your innocent love that drove you to attempt to revive your mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.28,0:17:01.83,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Your tremendous love that drove you to affix your brother's soul while prepared to throw your own life away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:07.46,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx97}Your unearthly determination that drove you to destroy your way out by burning down your home filled with memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:11.38,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Accept my embrace!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.38,0:17:14.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Get away! It's too hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.30,0:17:15.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.74,0:17:37.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you guys are at it already! So early in the morning, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:38.95,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,We've been working all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.79,0:17:47.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it's so late and you guys are still working!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.92,0:17:49.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be done pretty soon at this rate, won't ya?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:51.04,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Another all-nighter tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:52.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.31,0:18:05.14,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.81,0:18:13.90,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,They said they'd get it done in three days, so wait patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:21.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but I just can't sit still when I know a secret to the Philosopher's Stone lies in Central!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.79,0:18:27.75,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait! We're done!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:31.46,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You up for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:32.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.75,0:18:33.42,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.59,0:18:34.34,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Set...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:35.09,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.38,0:18:41.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This feeling of connecting my nerves gets me every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.76,0:18:46.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I won't have to deal with this pain once I get the Philosopher's Stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.77,0:18:49.89,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,That's too bad. You were a real money-spinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.81,0:18:54.40,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There's no need to go through the trouble of getting your limbs back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:57.19,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, what's wrong with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.19,0:18:59.90,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The smell of oil, the groaning of bearings...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:04.74,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,This beautiful form that was designed based on human engineering!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, how amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.20,0:19:08.54,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Automails, that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:09.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Machine freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.87,0:19:12.00,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, Alchemy freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:14.54,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,All right, it's complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.46,0:19:18.30,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.55,0:19:20.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Feels great!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.42,0:19:24.35,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,We raised the ratio of chromium this time so it would be more resistant to rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:28.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But that makes it less durable, so don't overuse-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.39,0:19:29.68,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.23,0:19:30.77,Default-alt,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al, sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:33.77,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be able to fix him quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.77,0:19:36.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There's a trick to it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.36,0:19:43.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This seal right here acts as the mediator between Al's soul and this suit,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.41,0:19:45.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,so I have to make sure I don't mess it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.00,0:19:54.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There! Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.58,0:19:55.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say we test it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.42,0:19:56.92,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:02.30,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,It'll get quiet around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.22,0:20:05.22,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.22,0:20:09.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to go find Dr. Marcoh's data at Central!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.39,0:20:11.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving on the first train tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.78,0:20:26.07,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He's sleeping with his belly out, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.07,0:20:27.53,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:29.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're like his guardian, Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.49,0:20:33.08,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain having such a needy brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.42,0:20:36.29,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,How old are you boys now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:39.59,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fourteen, and Brother is fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:48.18,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,He's so short, the same age as me,\Nand they call him a human weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.06,0:20:50.77,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Look how defenseless he is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.56,0:20:53.23,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a lot, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.44,0:20:56.56,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What's this formality all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:02.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You've always welcomed us as family. I'm really thankful of you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.61,0:21:07.24,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He might not say it, but Brother feels the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.03,0:21:08.78,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.62,0:21:11.95,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:14.66,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:17.54,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Granny... Winry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.38,0:21:19.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.55,0:21:25.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for everything, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.47,0:21:26.30,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:28.51,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Winry?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.51,0:21:30.72,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Her last few nights have all been all-nighters, so I bet she's exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.72,0:21:32.18,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to go wake her up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.18,0:21:34.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:37.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,She'll just keep on ranting about maintenance and all that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:37.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:40.90,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.23,0:21:44.74,Default,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,Stop by for a meal every once in a while, will ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.74,0:21:45.95,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.20,0:21:49.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Coming to a place so deep in the mountains just for a meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.99,0:21:53.74,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed, Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.70,0:21:56.00,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Have a safe trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:00.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.73,0:23:44.65,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I slept for the whole day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:49.03,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... this place turns into a battlefield whenever he comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.61,0:23:53.24,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.99,0:23:57.03,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.58,0:24:02.58,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Clues to the Philosopher's Stone are certainly there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.58,0:24:06.79,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, the enemy's evil hand has seized its target,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.79,0:24:14.09,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,and the boys are drawn into a labyrinth by the real truth that is beyond the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.09,0:24:18.26,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.26,0:24:21.27,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 7, Hidden Truths.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.23,0:24:25.86,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to reach it, you must not avert your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.86,0:24:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
